def: A kind of two-wheeled vehicle with seats back to back, thefront one somewhat elevated.
Being of a straw color. See Straw color, under Straw, n.
Antiq.) A military cloak worn by a general and his principalofficers.

An acid in which, to a greater or less extent, sulphur plays apart analogous to that of oxygen in an oxyacid; thus, thiosulphuricand sulpharsenic acids are sulphacids; -- called also sulphoacid. Seethe Note under Acid, n., 2.
The feast of All Saints, or Allhallows.To speak puling, like a beggar at Hallowmas. Shak.
Asparagus. [Colloq.] See the Note under Asparagus.
